\mathbb{N}
1 = P(\mathbb{N}) = P( \bigcup_{n=1}^{\infty} \{n\}) = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} P(\{n\}) =  \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} 0 = 0
p_n
\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} p_n = 1
p_n = \frac{1}{2^n}
n \in \mathbb{N}
P(\{n\}) = p_n
S \subset \mathbb{N}
P(S) = \sum_{n \in S} P(\{n\})
